[@matt](@FbGoHeEcePDG3Evemrc+hm+S77cXKf8BRQgkYinJggg=.ed25519)

I've been spending a bunch of time with MCSS and after playing around with the tokenizer I've got a huge tokenized object that I'd like to translate back into MCSS. Is there a way to do that? I was able to ~~steal~~ borrow some functions from `index.js` to take the tokenized object as input and produce CSS, but I'm having trouble taking the tokenized object as input and turning it back into MCSS.

Is there a reasonable way to do this, or have I entered the void of mayhem and confusion?
